==English==
===Etymology===
Shortened form of [[Plebeian]], the lower class in ancient Rome.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛb|-ɛb]]

===Noun===
'''pleb''' plural '''plebs'''

#Common people. Person out of their class at an event or gathering.
#Similar to the Icelandic word Plebbi: A pathetic person seeking wealth and fake happiness. A typical "low-life." This term is perfectly discribed in "Plebbabókin" (The book of pleb) by Icelandic comedian Jón Gnarr.

